Reasoning: The paper discusses the integration of information patterns in the modeling and design of mobility management services, which involves coordination strategies under various information and cooperation structures. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category, which deals with the study of systems composed of multiple interacting intelligent agents. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of local performance of the system using connected services, which may fall under the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category, which deals with the application of computational methods to engineering, finance, and scientific problems. The paper also discusses the use of incentive design and global objectives, which may fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category, which deals with the analysis and design of complex systems. Furthermore, the paper discusses the rise of mobile internet and the usage of mobile devices, which may fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category, which deals with the study of information processing and communication. Finally, the paper discusses the modeling and analysis of transportation systems, which may fall under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category, which deals with the design and analysis of computer networks and internet protocols.
